In R, which of the following command would result in a model through origin (or without intercepts)? 1. `lm(y ~ x + 0)` 2. `lm(y ~ 0 + x)` 3. `lm(y ~ x - 1)` 4. `lm(y ~ x)` #RStats #DataScience [TimeStamp:01102021123037]

Correct Ans: 1, 2 and 3 only. The operator `-` removes the specified terms. It can also be use to remove the intercept term, i.e. when fittign a linear model `y ~ x - 1` specifies a line through the origin. A model with no #RStats #DataScience [TimeStamp:01102021220006]
intercept can be also specified as `y ~ x + 0` or `y ~ 0 + x`. #RStats #DataScience [TimeStamp:01102021220006]
